Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.76,English,,0,0,0,,So this is a very exciting day because\N{\rChinese}于是今天是个非常激动人心的日子，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.76,0:00:06.60,English,,0,0,0,,we are officially starting the Gay to Lease journalism course.\N{\rChinese}我们正式开始了《盖伊·托·里斯》新闻学课程。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.98,0:00:09.56,English,,0,0,0,,Traditionally, we've understood journalism and\N{\rChinese}传统上，我们把新闻学理解为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.56,0:00:13.40,English,,0,0,0,,research as this method of just collecting information,\N{\rChinese}研究就是这种只收集信息的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.92,0:00:16.62,English,,0,0,0,,organizing it, and then expressing it.\N{\rChinese}组织它，然后表达它。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.92,0:00:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,But then along came a man named Gay to Lease, and he transformed journalism.\N{\rChinese}随后出现了一个叫盖伊·托·里斯的人，他改变了新闻学。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.96,0:00:25.96,English,,0,0,0,,He transformed the way we understood research. So\N{\rChinese}他改变了我们对研究的理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.96,0:00:31.82,English,,0,0,0,,we created something called literary journalism,\N{\rChinese}我们创造了一种叫作家新闻的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.20,0:00:34.86,English,,0,0,0,,which is the idea\N{\rChinese}这就是想法
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.86,0:00:39.16,English,,0,0,0,,that journalism can be by itself be literature.\N{\rChinese}新闻本身就能成为文学。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.20,0:00:44.76,English,,0,0,0,,The Gay to Lease method is going to teach us how to be creative, how to be imaginative,\N{\rChinese}盖伊·托·里斯方法将教会我们如何创造性、如何想象性
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.28,0:00:49.30,English,,0,0,0,,and how to engage with reality\N{\rChinese}以及如何与现实互动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.30,0:00:50.70,English,,0,0,0,,and engage with people.\N{\rChinese}并与人互动。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.86,0:00:52.54,English,,0,0,0,,We don't teach you this in school.\N{\rChinese}我们在学校里没有教你这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.68,0:00:53.88,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, we teach you the opposite.\N{\rChinese}实际上，我们教你的是相反的。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.08,0:00:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,We teach you the opposite. Don't explore. Just do what the teacher tells you to do.\N{\rChinese}我们教你的是相反的。别去探索，直接按老师说的去做。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.48,0:01:01.20,English,,0,0,0,,Where did he learn this? Well, he learned this at home.\N{\rChinese}他是从哪里学到的？嗯，学的就是在家里。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.28,0:01:04.14,English,,0,0,0,,The reason why is that\N{\rChinese}原因是因为……
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.14,0:01:07.30,English,,0,0,0,,his father was a tailor.\N{\rChinese}他的父亲是一名裁缝师。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.50,0:01:11.30,English,,0,0,0,,His father was a tailor.\N{\rChinese}他的父亲是一名裁缝师。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.68,0:01:19.62,English,,0,0,0,,And he had a tailoring business in New Jersey.\N{\rChinese}他在新泽西有一家裁缝生意。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.14,0:01:21.48,English,,0,0,0,,And his mother...\N{\rChinese}他的母亲……
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.56,0:01:27.94,English,,0,0,0,,took care of the business while his father made the clothes.\N{\rChinese}在父亲制作衣服时，他负责处理业务。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.12,0:01:33.78,English,,0,0,0,,So what does this have to do with exploration and reflection?\N{\rChinese}那这跟探索与反思有什么关系呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.82,0:01:40.70,English,,0,0,0,,Well, his mother was responsible for the business aspects.\N{\rChinese}好的，母亲负责店铺的业务。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.06,0:01:44.96,English,,0,0,0,,So these very wealthy people would come to the shop\N{\rChinese}于是这些非常富裕的人会来店里。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.96,0:01:47.82,English,,0,0,0,,and order very nice suits.\N{\rChinese}并订购非常好的西装。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.28,0:01:53.76,English,,0,0,0,,And her job was to deal with them.\N{\rChinese}她的工作就是与他们打交道。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.76,0:01:57.14,English,,0,0,0,,But it's actually very hard to deal with rich people.\N{\rChinese}但实际上与富人打交道非常难。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.32,0:01:58.58,English,,0,0,0,,They can be very demanding.\N{\rChinese}它们可能非常苛刻。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.26,0:02:01.90,English,,0,0,0,,So her strategy was to become their friend.\N{\rChinese}于是她的策略就是成为他们的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.58,0:02:04.38,English,,0,0,0,,And how do you become someone's friend?\N{\rChinese}[32] 那么你怎么才能成为别人的朋友？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.68,0:02:06.96,English,,0,0,0,,What do you do in order to become someone's friend?\N{\rChinese}[33] 你要做什么才能成为别人的朋友？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.26,0:02:08.64,English,,0,0,0,,What must you do? Talk.\N{\rChinese}你要做什么？说话。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.40,0:02:12.28,English,,0,0,0,,Wrong. Not talk.\N{\rChinese}错。不是说话。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.54,0:02:14.82,English,,0,0,0,,The opposite. Listen.\N{\rChinese}相反。听着。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.14,0:02:17.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Do you understand? So...\N{\rChinese}好的？你明白吗？所以…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.88,0:02:23.74,English,,0,0,0,,In the family living room, the mother would say,\N{\rChinese}在客厅里，妈妈会说，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.74,0:02:25.44,English,,0,0,0,,I want to sit down on the\N{\rChinese}我想坐在……上
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.44,0:02:30.52,English,,0,0,0,,couch talking with these very wealthy people.\N{\rChinese}沙发上与这些非常富有的人交谈。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:33.22,English,,0,0,0,,And she would talk just by listening.\N{\rChinese}她只靠倾听来交谈。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.02,0:02:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So her strategy for this is\N{\rChinese}好？她的做法是
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.36,0:02:42.96,English,,0,0,0,,that I am interested in you.\N{\rChinese}我对你有兴趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.44,0:02:48.18,English,,0,0,0,,So that's how she became friends with all these very wealthy people,\N{\rChinese}于是她就和这些富有的人交朋友了。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.36,0:02:50.12,English,,0,0,0,,even though she herself was not wealthy.\N{\rChinese}即使她自己不富有。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.30,0:02:52.66,English,,0,0,0,,She had a mindset that\N{\rChinese}她有一种心态，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.66,0:02:56.08,English,,0,0,0,,whoever came into her living room,\N{\rChinese}无论谁走进她的客厅，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.18,0:02:57.54,English,,0,0,0,,whoever was a client,\N{\rChinese}谁是客户，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.72,0:03:00.62,English,,0,0,0,,was first and foremost a friend.\N{\rChinese}先是朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.84,0:03:03.44,English,,0,0,0,,And she was interested in this person.\N{\rChinese}她对那个人很感兴趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.58,0:03:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,She was interested in people.\N{\rChinese}她对人很感兴趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.34,0:03:07.92,English,,0,0,0,,So she would spend hours and hours just listening to that\N{\rChinese}于是她会花上好几个小时，只是听那个人说说说。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:10.62,English,,0,0,0,,person talk and talk and talk.\N{\rChinese}她会花上好几个小时，只是听那个人说说说。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.10,0:03:13.48,English,,0,0,0,,And so you can say that this is exploration.\N{\rChinese}于是你可以说这是探索。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.50,0:03:19.56,English,,0,0,0,,Curiosity. Okay?\N{\rChinese}好奇。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.68,0:03:22.00,English,,0,0,0,,Exploration. But in the other room,\N{\rChinese}探索。可是在另一间房间，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.00,0:03:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,the father would by himself sit\N{\rChinese}父亲会亲自坐在那儿。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.14,0:03:27.30,English,,0,0,0,,and work on the clothes.\N{\rChinese}并且在衣服上工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.50,0:03:29.98,English,,0,0,0,,Right? I'm not sure if you've seen Taylor's work.\N{\rChinese}对吧？我不确定你是否看过泰勒的作品。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.24,0:03:31.64,English,,0,0,0,,They are very precise.\N{\rChinese}他们非常精准。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.16,0:03:33.54,English,,0,0,0,,They are very exact.\N{\rChinese}他们非常准确。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.92,0:03:35.46,English,,0,0,0,,They are very meticulous.\N{\rChinese}他们非常细致。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.44,0:03:37.68,English,,0,0,0,,They're very disciplined.\N{\rChinese}他们非常有纪律。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.92,0:03:40.84,English,,0,0,0,,They're very patient. So he could spend days\N{\rChinese}他们非常耐心。于是他可以在房间里花上几天时间专注于一件西装。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.84,0:03:45.38,English,,0,0,0,,and days in his room just working on a piece of suit.\N{\rChinese}他可以在房间里花上几天时间专注于一件西装。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:48.06,English,,0,0,0,,Right? This is the idea of reflection.\N{\rChinese}对吧？这就是反思的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.00,0:03:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,The pursuit of perfection.\N{\rChinese}追求完美。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.06,0:04:00.60,English,,0,0,0,,So exploration is the pursuit of curiosity.\N{\rChinese}探索是好奇心的追求。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.54,0:04:08.10,English,,0,0,0,,And reflection is the pursuit of perfection.\N{\rChinese}反思是完美的追求。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.88,0:04:14.12,English,,0,0,0,,This is a Gay Talese research method.\N{\rChinese}这是一种《Gay Talese》研究方法。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:15.64,English,,0,0,0,,This is what I'll be teaching you.\N{\rChinese}这就是我要教给你的内容。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.78,0:04:19.44,English,,0,0,0,,This is something that will not just help you become a better writer,\N{\rChinese}这不仅能让你写作更好，也会让你更具创意、更有效的研究者。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.44,0:04:23.36,English,,0,0,0,,but someone who will be much more creative and a much more effective researcher.\N{\rChinese}这将使你成为更好的作家，并且更具创意、更有效的研究者。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.92,0:04:26.54,English,,0,0,0,,So even if you are going to the sciences,\N{\rChinese}所以即使你去科学领域，我保证你在这门课学到的技能无论去哪里都能派上用场。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.92,0:04:31.70,English,,0,0,0,,I guarantee you that the skills you'll be learning in this class will help you wherever you go.\N{\rChinese}我保证你在这门课学到的技能无论去哪里都能派上用场。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.94,0:04:35.20,English,,0,0,0,,I want you to go around Beijing and take pictures.\N{\rChinese}我想让你在北京四处走走，拍下照片。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.52,0:04:36.98,English,,0,0,0,,Again, the idea is contrast.\N{\rChinese}再次，核心是对比。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.66,0:04:41.10,English,,0,0,0,,Remember that here he says, New York is a city of things unnoticed.\N{\rChinese}记住这里他说：纽约是一座不被注意到的事物之城。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.60,0:04:43.72,English,,0,0,0,,New York is a city of contrast.\N{\rChinese}纽约是一座对比之城。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.28,0:04:46.68,English,,0,0,0,,I want you to do the same thing for Beijing.\N{\rChinese}我想让你在北京也做同样的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.84,0:04:49.42,English,,0,0,0,,Take your camera and take pictures of contrast.\N{\rChinese}拿起相机，拍下对比的画面。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.42,0:04:51.36,English,,0,0,0,,Things that other people would not notice.\N{\rChinese}别人不注意到的事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.58,0:04:55.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And take pictures of things that are contrast of each other.\N{\rChinese}好的？再拍下互相对比的事物。
